# Lobster WhatsApp Connector — Config Example
#
# Copy relevant settings to ~/.config/lobster/whatsapp.env (user secrets, NOT in git)
# or to ~/lobster-workspace/config/whatsapp.env (legacy location, also not in git).
#
# The systemd service loads this file via:
#   EnvironmentFile=-~/.config/lobster/whatsapp.env
#
# All settings are optional — defaults are shown below.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Session storage
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Where Baileys stores its multi-file auth state (credentials + keys).
# This directory is created automatically on first run.
# Per-user — do NOT share across Lobster instances.
# Default: ~/.config/lobster/whatsapp-session
#
# WHATSAPP_SESSION_PATH=~/.config/lobster/whatsapp-session

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Identity
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Lobster's own WhatsApp JID (e.g. 15551234567@c.us).
# Auto-detected on first run — the bridge prints it as [READY] Detected Lobster JID: ...
# Copy that value here after your first QR scan.
# Required for group @mention filtering to work correctly.
#
# WHATSAPP_LOBSTER_JID=15551234567@c.us

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Access control
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Comma-separated whitelist of WhatsApp JIDs allowed to send messages to Lobster.
# If empty (default), all DMs are accepted.
# Recommended for personal use: set this to your own number to prevent strangers
# from interacting with Lobster if they somehow get the linked number.
#
# WHATSAPP_ALLOWED_JIDS=15551234567@c.us,15559876543@c.us

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# IPC directories (file-based message passing)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Directory where the bridge writes incoming message events as JSON files.
# The Python adapter (whatsapp_bridge_adapter.py) watches this directory.
# Default: ~/messages/wa-events
#
# WA_EVENTS_DIR=~/messages/wa-events

# Directory where the Python adapter writes outgoing message commands.
# The bridge watches this directory and sends them via WhatsApp.
# Default: ~/messages/wa-commands
#
# WA_COMMANDS_DIR=~/messages/wa-commands

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Health monitoring
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# File that the bridge touches on each received message.
# Used by health-check scripts to detect a dead bridge.
# Default: ~/lobster-workspace/logs/whatsapp-heartbeat
#
# WA_HEARTBEAT_FILE=~/lobster-workspace/logs/whatsapp-heartbeat
